decks.notes: The main concept of this deck is to control the opponent's actions and disrupt their strategy. It employs a wide variety of control spells such as counterspells (Force of Will, Counterspell), discard spells (Thoughtseize, Duress), and removal spells (Fatal Push, Swords to Plowshares) to prevent the opponent from developing their board or executing their game plan. The deck also includes tutors (Demonic Tutor, Enlightened Tutor) to search for specific answers or win conditions. It aims to maintain a strong grip on the game by using powerful planeswalkers (Jace, the Mind Sculptor, Teferi, Time Raveler) and card advantage engines (Future Sight, Mystic Confluence) to out-value the opponent. Additionally, the deck includes a mix of versatile and efficient removal spells (Abrupt Decay, Toxic Deluge) to handle various threats.

This deck focuses on utilizing counterspells, bounce effects, and card advantage to control the board and disrupt the opponent's strategy. With Venser, Shaper Savant as the commander, the deck aims to consistently bounce threats and disrupt the opponent's game plan. The inclusion of powerful spells like Force of Will, Cryptic Command, and Mystic Confluence provide additional ways to control the game. By using cards like Narset, Parter of Veils and Hullbreacher to limit the opponent's resources, and maintaining a high count of Islands to support cards like Back to Basics, this deck aims to outvalue and outmaneuver the opponent in a slow and methodical game plan.
